Updated ADH Face Covering Directive:

Masks with valves are not allowed. Bandanas and single-layer neck gaiters (a form of mask made out of stretchy, moisture-wicking fabric that is worn around the neck and pulled up over the nose and mouth) may not provide sufficient protection and are strongly discouraged. Bandanas and gaiters may be doubled to provide two layers of protection.

Anna Hanks‎Green Forest News and Views
August 19 at 10:54 AM ·

Kindergarten Meet and Greet is TOMORROW! 😊❤️🐾 If you haven’t registered your child or completed their file, please do so soon, so we can schedule a Kindergarten Meet and Greet time. Under current ADH guidance, visitors will not be allowed in the school except the reception area. This includes the first day of school. School officials will help your child find their classroom on the first day. Kindergarten Meet and Greet is a great opportunity to show your child their classroom and get a “first day” picture with their Kindergarten teacher if you so choose. K teachers are excited to see and meet you SOON!! 😊

This year we will be implementing our “Feed the Tigers”program. This will include the following:

Pre Game Meals
Post Game Meals
Cases of Water
Snacks for locker Rooms
Locker Room Decoration

If you are a parent, teacher/administrator, community leader, business owner, pastor, Church leader, etc. and you would like to help out with Feed the Tigers this year, please come meet with Coach Tibbitt Tuesday 8/18 after practice (6pm) in the Green Forest Field House Parking Lot to discuss these plans...Please wear a mask.

If you would like to help but are unable to come to the meeting, please message me through this page.

Thank you! Go Tigers!

Miss Carroll County Pageant
August 7 at 10:04 AM ·

Last night at the Fair Board meeting it was decided to hold the 2020 Miss Carroll County Pageant virtually. The Arkansas State Fair has also decided that they will hold the preliminary rounds of the 2020 pageant virtually as well. We all decided this was the best outcome for everyone.

The pageant will be held September 12, 2020; this is for Junior and Miss ONLY. Contestants who have already entered please contact us at 870-654-0229 or 870-480-6031. We will still accept entries until Saturday, August 29, 2020.

We are very excited to be able to still hold the pageant and hope everyone is as well. If you have any questions please contact us 870-654-0229 or 870-480-6031 or you can email us at misscarrollcountypageant@gmail.com

Green Forest Choirs
July 24 at 8:56 PM ·

Congratulations to the members of the Chamber Choir for the 2020-2021 school year!

This was NOT an easy decision by any means. I know this year's auditions were an anomaly, considering our current situation. I took extra care in trying to make the best of it for the students. If you were not selected for Chamber Choir this year, I genuinely hope that you audition again next year. If you would like to discuss your audition, I'd be happy to answer questions via email.

I don't have all the information about what this year is going to look like for us, but we will adjust and make the best of it. That's what Tigers do!

Congratulations again to those selected, and see you all soon.

Mrs. Duarte-Black

Please complete this form to request to participate in the Green Forest Schools Virtual (Online) Learning Option for the 2020-2021 school year.

Parents who have multiple students will complete a different form for each student.

DEADLINE: MONDAY, AUGUST 3

VIRTUAL/ONLINE LEARNING:
-All instruction will be online; no in person or on campus instruction
-Students will learn remotely full time
-Students will be required to be onsite for state-mandated assessments
-Students who fall significantly behind or fail to complete assignments may be removed from online learning
-Students enrolled in virtual learning must remain through the end of the current nine week grading period but may return for onsite instruction at the beginning of the following grading period

Paper copies are available in each campus office.

https://forms.gle/anDr5xDSWsXoDG5Y8

https://forms.gle/mrtwpn9nLFDAhzCc7

Please take a few minutes and review the options for our revised school calendar and make your selection. The survey will be available until Wednesday, July 15 at 5:00PM.

There are 2 options for making up the 7 days from moving the start of school from August 13 to August 24.

Option 1 is adding all days to the end with the last day being June 2

Option 2 is going to school the Monday of Thanksgiving Break (November 23), February 15, then adding 4 days to the end and the last day on May 28.

Green Forest, Arkansas FFA Chapter
July 9 at 2:11 PM ·

Congratulations to our FFA CDE teams that competed in the virtual State CDE's.

The Meats Evaluation team placed 3rd in state. Alex Kilbourn was 6th high individual and Alex Leal was 9th high individually.

In the Poultry CDE, our team placed 6th in state. Sara Reyes was 6th overall individually.

Once again, congratulations to these teams on having an outstanding year!!!!

En cuanto a la reciente experiencia escolar de sus hijos:

Green Forest Schools
May 28 at 8:38 AM ·

Estimados padres, estudiantes y maestros:

Estamos enviando una encuesta muy importante para recopilar información concerniendo al semestre de primavera que acabamos de cursar y al próximo año escolar. Pueden encontrar esta encuesta a través de Facebook, en la página web escolar o pueden obtener una copia en papel de ser necesario. Por favor, completen la encuesta antes del 5 de junio. shared_text:
Rob Kerby‎Green Forest News and Views
May 15 at 4:52 PM ·

Caps and gowns and umbrellas! Tonight, Friday, May 15, at 6 p.m., a bunch of Green Forest moms have planned a drive-by parade for the GFHS Class of 2020 in front of Cattlemen's Restaurant on Main Street.

"We are going forward as planned," says Jodie Parsons DeMeyer with the Tigers Booster Club. "I told the kids to bring umbrellas!"

The plan is for graduates to stand six feet apart from each other in front of Cattlemen's, waving at friends, family and Tiger fans driving past honking, flashing lights and blowing kisses.

The procession will start on Olive Street between Blaine Andrews' Town & Country Veterinary Clinic and the back doors of First Baptist Church -- then will proceed past the grads and exit the Cattlemen's parking lot at the Butterball Feed Mill.

Come and support our kids! It'll take 15 minutes! Honk, wave and let 'em know Green Forest loves 'em big time!

Green Forest Water Department
May 12 at 3:33 PM ·

Please please fill out your Census.
You can help get money for Green Forest.

How? By filling out your Census form.

Green Forest Mayor Jerry Carlton has a special request. Our city receives federal and state funding based on our population -- which is determined by the U.S. Census.

But we have a problem. The Green Forest post office says that a large number of local Census forms were returned because the addresses have no mailboxes.

If you have a PO Box you will not receive a census form. You can go online and put your census in at
2020census.gov
Please do this for Green Forest.

If you have received no Census form -- call 844-330-2020 to talk to a Census worker in English. In Spanish: 844-468-2020.

This is Mr. Booth, High School Principal, at Green Forest Schools. On behalf of myself, Mrs. Tackett, Middle School Principal, Mrs. Anderson, Intermediate Principal and Mrs.Chaney, Elementary Principal we hope this message finds all of you well. At this time, we want to announce that all AMI packets are due to be completed and turned in to the appropriate building drop off location so that they can be recorded, no later than Thursday, May 21, 2020. This is the official last day of school. Please remember that there is a drop off cabinet at each building or you can give them to the people delivering the breakfast/lunch meals. We also want you to know that we miss you and hope that everyone is staying safe. Thank you

Arkansas PBS
April 14 at 12:08 PM ·

We’re thrilled to announce that “Arkansas AMI” will continue to support at-home learning in partnership with the Arkansas Department of Education for the remainder of the school year, ending May 22!

Our educational programming and classroom materials — created in partnership with the Arkansas Department of Education’s Division of Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE) - will continue to be available via daily broadcasts, live streaming at myarkansaspbs.org/live, on demand and archived at myarkansaspbs.org/arkansasami, the free Engage Arkansas PBS app for iPhone and Android, the PBS Video app for mobile and smart devices and on the Arkansas PBS channel for YouTube TV subscribers.

Learn more in our full press release: myarkansaspbs.org/engage/pressroom/arkansas_pbs_to_continue_ami_broadcasts_for_remainder_of_school_year

Week 1 of food distribution to our families has been a success! We are currently serving approximately 500 meals including a breakfast and lunch each day to kids in our area.

Preparing these meals with a very limited staff hasn’t been easy but we are glad to be able to provide for all as needed. All the smiles and thank you’s we receive from our students and parents makes it so worthwhile.

A big thanks to Harps of Green Forest for supplying plastic bags to help our families transport their food and drinks.

#WeLoveOurTigers

To The Class of 2020 and their Families:

According to Governor Hutchinson’s recent announcements, the seniors who are in good standing at the end of the 3rd quarter have met the Arkansas requirements for Graduation.

If you are currently in the process of credit recovery or are enrolled in AP courses, you will need to work for completion.

We are all concerned about the Graduation Ceremony. At this time we are unable to make plans. We will look at all options when we are given the all clear.

shared_text:
U.S. Census Bureau
March 18 at 1:07 PM ·

Beginning today, in support of guidance on what we can all do to help slow the spread of coronavirus, #2020Census field operations will be suspended for two weeks until April 1, 2020. We're taking this step to help protect the health and safety of the American public, Census Bureau employees, and everyone going through the hiring process for temporary census taker positions. During this pause in field operations, the Census Bureau will continue to evaluate all 2020 Census operations. Should any additional adjustments need to be made, the Census Bureau will communicate these changes broadly and promptly. The public is strongly encouraged to respond to the 2020 Census online using a desktop computer, laptop, smartphone, or tablet, and can also respond by phone or mail. Read the full statement: https://go.usa.gov/xdzXx

shared_text:
Rob Kerby‎Green Forest News and Views
March 20 at 1:34 PM ·

Green Forest’s young Tigers showed up big time Friday morning to give away 100 boxes of food at the Learning Center across from the fire station. Unloading boxes, then giving them to families driving up was hard work.

Thanks to former Miss Green Forest Ruby Bustamante! To eighth grader Pablo Moreno, referee coordinator for Green Forest youth soccer! Seventh grader Arauny Reyes from Templo Emanuel church!

A big thanks to GFHS soccer varsity player Blue Doh Soh, seventh grader Bible One and all their buddies from the Karen Baptist Church.

And of course, thanks to all the adults, too. But it was dadgum inspirational watching Green Forest’s future leaders stepping up, stacking boxes and working the car lane, making sure everybody got served!

We were out of boxes by noon. Good job, kids!

I hope this message finds you well! This email is for all parents and guardians of Green Forest students.
We are working on our School Improvement Plan for the
2020 - 2021 school year. One part of the process is determine our "needs" based on data and information available to us.

In order to help us with this process, attached you will find a Google survey addressing Title funds that we receive and how the district spends those funds. Please do you best to complete and submit the survey by March 31st. Your prompt completion would be greatly appreciated. Your child may assist you with their gmail account in completion.
Your input is greatly appreciated!
Thank you,
Mr. Darnell

Green Forest Schools tendrá clases el lunes, 16 de marzo. Empezando el martes 17 al viernes 30 de marzo, utilizaremos el paquete AMI días 2 a 5. Los autobuses correrán sus rutas normales el lunes, 16 de marzo. No habrá tutoría después de clases el lunes. Todas las actividades deportivas están canceladas este martes a viernes, 17 a 20 de marzo. La junta de la Mesa Directiva se llevará a cabo el lunes, marzo 16 a las 5:00pm.

Los paquetes AMI para días 6 a 10 se entregarán a los estudiantes mañana después de la 1:00 pm. Si su estudiante no está presente en la escuela, entonces un adulto puede recoger su paquete de AMI en la escuela el lunes después de la 1:00 pm o el martes,17 al viernes, 20.

Tendremos nuestras vacaciones de primavera empezando el lunes, 23 al viernes, 27 de marzo. Las clases resumirán el lunes, 30 el marzo.

Green Forest Schools WILL BE OPEN on Monday, March 16. Tuesday through Friday (March 17-20) will be AMI Days 2-5. Buses will run as normal on Monday. No after school tutoring on Monday or until school resumes. All athletic facilities will be closed Tuesday through Friday, March 17-20. School Board Meeting will be held as scheduled on Monday at 5PM.

Packets containing AMI Days 6-10 will be passed out to students tomorrow after 1:00PM. If your child is not in attendance at school, a parent may pick up the AMI packet from the school on Monday after 1:00PM or Tuesday through Friday.

Spring Break is March 23-27. School will resume on Monday, March 30.

Rob Kerby shared a post to the group: Green Forest News and Views.

Don't think you're good enough? We believe in teaching you. Nobody sits on the bench. Everybody plays. Hey, go watch the high school varsity Tigers ... quietly we'll point out at least three top players who had to learn everything as junior highs.

They had "want to" -- that desire to prove to themselves that they were athletes. And we just cheered them on!

Green Forest Soccer
March 4 at 8:16 AM ·

First practice is Tuesday, March 17, at 6 p.m. -- for 4 year olds thru eighth graders. Everybody gets a home game every Tuesday and Thursday at 6 p.m. at the Green Forest city park soccer fields.

Sixth, seventh and eighth graders also have the option of playing away games on Saturdays -- and we've got our eye on entering the Arkansas State Cup.

Pea Ridge School District
January 9 at 10:47 PM ·

It is with heavy hearts that we inform you that Pea Ridge student, Ayden Cotton, passed away today. Ayden was a sophomore and an outstanding young man. He was a son, a brother, a friend and so much more. In this time of loss and tragedy we encourage families and students to take time for reflection, remembrance, and togetherness.

We will have all district counselors available for students and teachers starting at 7:15 am tomorrow in the Counseling Center. Pastors will also be on standby for student, staff and community.
